originalText.text:
I can't say anything about Ms. Malkin as a PT, but as a business owner she needs to clean house. Not only did her office assistants send invoices to an address not even near me, they went and charged a huge amount without authorization, without speaking to me and then when I called copped a huge attitude because THEY messed up. The office manager even admitted on the phone that both invoices were returned to the practice, but did they call or email to get the correct mailing address or find out what the issue is?

I do not simply send money without an invoice, especially as I need to verify everything with my insurance company. There are a ton of physical therapy offices in NYC, use any one of those other ones.
